	<p>
<p>Many
attorneys wrestle with the idea of using professional <b>records retrieval services</b>. They know that their staff could easily
handle the task on their own – so why incur the extra cost? In reality, a
professional records service can actually be highly beneficial in certain
circumstances. It can save on time, provide better results, and often is more
cost-effective than handling it in-house.</p>
<p>Not sure
if professional records retrieval services are right for your current case?
Just ask yourself these questions: </p>

<p>·<span>&nbsp;
</span><b>Are you on a tight deadline?</b> If you’re short on time, then you
need to put your records request in the hands of a true professional – someone
who can get the job done as accurately and quickly as possible. If you don’t,
you could find yourself without a key piece of evidence when it comes time to
present your case.</p>

<p>·<span>&nbsp; </span><b>Do you have a small staff?</b> Consider this: if your staff is small, can you really afford
to have one of your few employees consumed by record request tasks? Do you want
them spending all their time filling out forms, making calls and sending faxes?
Or do you have more pressing matters they could be tending to? If so, then a
professional records service may be a more fitting solution.</p>

<p>·<span>&nbsp; </span><b>Is your case complicated?</b> If your case is complex or requires hard-to-get records,
then it’s probably a task best left to the pros. A professional records service
will know best how to get the job done and get it done right. In fact, they’ve
probably handled a case just like yours before! </p>

<p>·<span>&nbsp;
</span><b>Do you have more important tasks to work
on?</b> Sure, you could
handle the records requests yourself, but do you really have time for that?
Wouldn’t your time be better spent connecting with clients, gathering evidence
or marketing your firm? If yes, then hand your records requests off to a
professional service, and get back to the more important tasks at hand.</p>

<p></p>

<p>If you
answered yes to any of these questions, then you could definitely benefit from
using professional <b>records retrieval
services</b>. Contact LORR today to get started!</p>

<br></p>
